The estate of{Donibristle}was given to Thomas Randolph,1st Earl of Moray by Robert the Bruce as a reward for capturing Edinburgh Castle.
The first building was ruined by fire in{1592}when the Earl was murdered.It was rebuilt in the 18th century.This building was gutted by fire in{1858} and demolished c.1912. The only part to escape destruction were the servants quarters.Of the surviving buildings the most striking feature is the wrought iron screen between the two wings.The west wing was damaged by fire in{1984.}
Northwest of the house stands the private chapel of the Morays.Now an unsafe ruin,there are however{17 lead {coffins,}the last of which was buried in 1895,in it's crypt.
